<br>
I have seen a number of memorial topics across a few of the boards Suzy went to, but the places you should really check out are as follows:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://go.ezboard.com/bluheaven"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  blu's heaven</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Suzy's board, which we are going to keep running.  Suzy would never have wanted her board to die.  By the way, this board has not been renamed by us - I think it is a very poignant reminder of her.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.bbarden.com/dreams/index.html"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Colour Dreams web site</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://go.ezboard.com/bcolourdreams"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Colour Dreams ezboard</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - these were dedicated to the love I have for Suzy and vice versa.  Suzy and I used to &quot;bounce&quot; poems off one another - I'd write a poem, she'd write a few poems, I'd write some more.  It was tough to see how I could continue to write when I knew I wasn't going to get Suzy's responses in return <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/puppydogeyes.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ... but I don't think that Colour Dreams should end prematurely.  I have been informed by Suzy's brother that she has written a huge amount of poetry I didn't even know about, so I will try and publish some of that in Colour Dreams to remember her by.<br>
<br>
If any of you wish to see how strong the bond between us was, Colour Dreams is the place to go.<br>
<br>
Thanks again... you don't know how much this means to me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/em/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
